      • doSleep

        protected static boolean doSleep(long millis)
        Causes the currently executing thread to sleep (temporarily cease execution) for the specified number of milliseconds. The thread does not lose ownership of any monitors.

        Unlike Thread.sleep(long), this method does not throw an InterruptedException. Instead, it traps the exception and returns a boolean indicating whether it was interrupted. In addition, it will set the interrupt status of the thread correctly so Thread.interrupted() returns the correct value.

        Parameters:
        millis - the length of time to sleep in milliseconds.
        Returns:
        whether the thread was interrupted while sleeping
        See Also:
        Thread.sleep(long)
